          "Italian doesn't just use words. It uses",
          "HANDS. A gesture can replace, amplify,",
          "or contradict what's spoken.",
          "",
          "This isn't caricature \u2014 it's a shared",
          "visual language, codified over centuries.",
          "Bruno Munari catalogued the system in",
          "1958. Most gestures are still current.",
          "",
          "THE BASICS:",
          "",
          "ma che vuoi?  = fingers pinched tips-up,",
          "   hand moves up-down slightly.",
          "   'what the hell do you want?'",
          "",
          "perfetto!     = thumb + index pinched,",
          "   lips kiss the fingertips. Seal of",
          "   approval for food, art, beauty."
        ],
